78	/// The router type for composing handlers and services.
79	///
80	/// `Router<S>` means a router that is _missing_ a state of type `S` to be able
81	/// to handle requests. Thus, only `Router<()>` (i.e. without missing state) can
82	/// be passed to [`serve`]. See [`Router::with_state`] for more details.
